720229f-a.title: Manhattan: Greenwich Street - Spring Street
720229f-a.text:
(1)
Greenwich Street, east side, at Spring Street, Nos. 501-513 Greenwich Street, at, adjoining and south of the S.E. corner of Spring Street, are frame houses with brick fronts; Ninth Ave., Elevated on Greewich Street, obstructing the view.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 567.
(2)
The same, showing a rear view of Nos. 505-509 Greenwich Street, south of the S.E. corner of Spring Street. No 507 is a 4-story
building.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 578.

723391f-a.text:
(1)
315-311 Spring Street, at and adjoining the N.E. corner of Greenwich Street. Three old houses which will be demolished prior to 1910 to make way for the Cornell & Underhill warehouse, 309-317 Spring Street and 515-521 Greenwich Street.
About 1908.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, another view.
About 1908.

(3)
